tring",...]\}, ... ], "Pillar_B_Domain_Discipline": [ \{"term": "string", "synonyms": ["string",...]\}, ... ] \} Each object in the arrays should represent a distinct concept. The "term" should be the most representative keyword, and "synonyms" should be a list of alternative phrasings or acronyms. # FEW-SHOT_EXAMPLE ## Example Input Text: "This paper introduces a comprehensive taxonomy for FM-based agents, developed through a systematic literature review (SLR). This taxonomy categorizes the architectural options of FM-based agents. Our goal is to provide a structured framework for analyzing design choices in agent-based systems." ## Example JSON Output for the above text: \{ "Pillar_A_Technology": [ \{"term": "FM-based agent", "synonyms": ["Foundation Model-based agent"]\} ], "Pillar_B_Domain_Discipline": [ \{"term": "taxonomy", "synonyms": ["classification", "framework"]\}, \{"term": "architectural option", "synonyms": ["design choice"]\}, \{"term": "systematic literature review", "synonyms":\}, \{"term": "agent-based systems", "synonyms":\} ] \} # INPUT_TEXT Analyze the following text: \{text_to_be_analyzed\}}